# Script versioning

When changing any script under `scripts/` or `install.sh`, bump the **first** version comment line (newest entry, within the first 40 lines).

## Format

```bash
# v. YYYYMMDD.HH24MISS - short description of this change
```

- Use local wall-clock time when you edit (24-hour `HHMMSS`, zero-padded).
- Keep one new line at the top of the changelog block (after shebang / `# shellcheck` line).
- Older changelog lines may stay for history; only the first matching line is parsed.

## Examples

```bash
#!/usr/bin/env bash
# v. 20260716.162603 - quit when no new RSS edition on server
# v. 20260716.162601 - adopt YYYYMMDD.HH24MISS versioning scheme
```

```bash
# shellcheck shell=bash
# v. 20260716.162602 - validate economist.local.conf before pipeline starts
```

## Parsing

`install.sh` (`economist_parse_script_version`) and `economist-script-reinstall.sh` read this format. Install table shows `v. 20260716.162603`.

Legacy `# YYYY.MM.DD - v. N.N - ...` lines are still parsed for old installed copies only — do not add new legacy lines.
